                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d552">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Johnson, Louis A./33: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Personal Representative of the President in India</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-13T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 13, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>197. Personal for Colonel Johnson. Your 276, May 9, 9 p.m. The President, who has
                    been consulted regarding your proposed return to the United States, did not
                    recall that such a time table had been agreed upon. The President feels that
                    your return to this country at the time proposed would be subject to
                    misinterpretation both here and abroad and he hopes your plans can be adjusted
                    accordingly.</p>
                <p>I am sorry to learn of your illness and I hope you are now well on the road to
                    recovery.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
